<HL>
   International Brief -- Blue Circle Industries PLC:
   Building-Materials Firm Says
   '89 Pretax Profit Rose 14%
</HL>
<DATE>
04/26/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   U.BCI
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Blue Circle Industries PLC, a British building-materials
concern, said pretax profit for 1989 rose 14%, with its
United Kingdom cement operation reporting significant
earnings growth despite a general downturn in the British
construction industry.
   Blue Circle said pretax profit increased to #231.8 million
($378.8 million) from #203.1 million. Sales rose 14% to #1.28
billion from #1.12 billion. Profit after tax less minority
interests rose 6.3% to #163.0 million from #153.3 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company reported an extraordinary gain of #23.3
million, resulting in a 30% rise in net profit attributable
to shareholders, to #186.3 million from #143.7 million. In
the previous year, Blue Circle reported an extraordinary loss
of #9.6 million.
   The company said its British cement division increased
operating profit by 48%, while its property division and U.S.
operations reported a drop in earnings.
</TEXT>
